nce the pot begins to boil, the collards will have wilted enough to give it all a stir without everything spilling out. Stir everything up good then place the lid back on top, reduce the heat to low and let simmer until the collards are to the desired tenderness (I simmered for two hours). Stir every 15 minutes or so."], "images": [{"url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TUiHW8O3e9I/AAAAAAAACoI/qa0mahO4eAk/s800/Beer%20Braised%20Collards%202.jpg", "path": "full/bb40c714457b7a81d7bb22b50d692cae3682ade3.jpg", "checksum": "cd7b732eded9c1c496dec278fbbe73a9"}], "link": "http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/02/beer-braised-collard-greens/", "recipe_cook_time": ["PT2M"], "recipe_yield": ["6"]}